$interpreted: : 2 years later
Kittyeyes: Here, be careful when carrying the wheat. If you don't have enough, there's more over here.
Old Man: Thank you so much, Kittyeyes. The village's harvest had not been particularly good these last years. If not for your assistance, we would have long...
Kittyeyes: No worries. We're neighbors; it's natural that we help each other out.
Male Villager: We ask you and Koll to bring us supplies all the time. Really don't know how we're going to repay you guys...
Old Man: I remember, today is Kittyeyes' birthday!
Koll: ARO!
Male Villager: Is that true? Then we have to prepare a birthday present for you! What do you want?
Kittyeyes: It's fine, you don't have to go through the trouble to...
Old Man: Out of the question. This is a rare opportunity for us to repay you. We won't take "no" for an answer, sister!
Kittyeyes: Hmm...I do really want the fur of a Prickear Monkey from Whistlewood Valley. Heard it makes warm clothes, but the journey is too far and too risky...
Kittyeyes: I say a cake would be perfectly fine for me.
Male Villager: Sure. Then we will bake a birthday cake for you together!
Kittyeyes: Thank you~
Koll: Grrrrrr~~
Aosta: Hmm? The wolf cub that follows Kittyeyes and Roger all the time? You've grown quite a bit.
Koll: Grrrrrr~~
Aosta: ...The traits are not obvious when you're a cub; turns out you're a Glimmer Wolf? What a rare sight to witness a living specimen...
？？？: Happy birthday, Kittyeyes!
Kittyeyes: Thank you, Roger. How did you know that I want a coat made from the fur of a Prickear Monkey?
Roger: What good is a brother if he can't tell what his little sister is thinking? I purchased it a long time ago from a mechanican merchant.
Roger: Just waiting for your birthday.

Kittyeyes: This birthday present is awesome, Thank you!
When Koll comes back, I'll definitely show it off to him!
Roger: Koll didn't come back from the village with you?
Kittyeyes: Yeah, no idea where he went. He probably just wandered off. What a troublesome pet.
